definitions.definition: A thin and usually jagged space opened in a previously solid material.
examples: A large crack had formed in the roadway.

definitions.definition: A narrow opening.
examples: We managed to squeeze through a crack in the rock wall.

definitions.definition: A sharply humorous comment; a wisecrack .
examples: I didn't appreciate that crack about my hairstyle.

definitions.definition: ( slang ) Crack cocaine , a potent, relatively cheap, addictive variety of cocaine ; often a rock , usually smoked through a crack-pipe .

subdefinitions.definition: ( figurative , humorous ) Something good-tasting or habit-forming.

definitions.definition: ( onomatopoeia ) The sharp sound made when solid material breaks .
examples: The crack of the falling branch could be heard for miles.

definitions.definition: ( onomatopoeia ) Any sharp sound .
examples: The crack of the bat hitting the ball.

definitions.definition: A sharp , resounding blow .
( informal ) An attempt at something .
examples: I'd like to take a crack at that game.

definitions.definition: ( vulgar , slang ) The vagina .
( informal ) The space between the buttocks .
examples: Pull up your pants! Your crack is showing.

definitions.definition: ( Northern England , Scotland , Ireland ) Conviviality ; fun ; good conversation, chat, gossip, or humorous storytelling; good company.
examples: He's good crack . [It's nice having him around]

definitions.definition: ( Northern England , Scotland , Ireland ) Business ; events ; news .
examples: What's this crack about a possible merger?

definitions.definition: ( computing ) A program or procedure designed to circumvent restrictions or usage limits on software.
examples: Has anyone got a crack for DocumentWriter 3.0?

definitions.definition: ( hydrodynamics , US , dated ) An expanding circle of white water surrounding the site of a large explosion at shallow depth, marking the progress of the shock wave through the air above the water. A nuclear explosion in shallow water; the crack is clearly visible on the water's surface.
( Cumbria , elsewhere throughout the North of the UK ) a meaningful chat.
( Internet slang ) Extremely silly , absurd or off-the-wall ideas or prose.
The tone of voice when changed at puberty .
( archaic ) A mental flaw ; a touch of craziness ; partial insanity .
( archaic ) A crazy or crack-brained person.
( obsolete ) A boast ; boasting.
( obsolete ) Breach of chastity .
( obsolete ) A boy , generally a pert , lively boy.
( slang , dated , UK ) A brief time; an instant ; a jiffy .
examples: I'll be with you in a crack .

definitions.definition: ( African-American Vernacular , dated ) The act of hitting on someone.
( obsolete , gypsy slang ) Dry firewood .
